21/04/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski and Tirana Mayor Edi Rama, leader of the opposition Socialist Party in Albania, reaffirmed their common desire to boost bilateral ties, during a meeting Thursday (20 April) in Skopje. 
Talks focused on promoting regional co-operation, business partnerships and investment. 
(Macedonian Government Web site, MIA - 21/04/06)
